      <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-2xl font-bold uppercase sm:text-3xl text-oak">Introducing</h2>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center mb-6 gap-x-4 sm:flex-nowrap">
        <h1 class="w-full mb-4 font-serif text-4xl font-bold uppercase sm:w-auto sm:text-5xl text-oak sm:mb-0">
          The Queen
        </h1>
        <hr class="w-4/5 mx-auto border-2 sm:w-auto sm:flex-1 border-oak sm:mx-0">
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg">
        <p>
          The queen is the most powerful piece on the board, combining the moves of both the rook and bishop. It can
          move any number of squares in a straight line, either horizontally, vertically, or diagonally.
        </p>
        <p>
          The queen is most effective when it is active and centralized, where it can influence both sides of the board.
          Mastering the queen's movements and understanding its tactical potential is crucial for dominating the game
          and launching devastating attacks!
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="flex flex-col-reverse items-center mb-32 lg:flex-row lg:gap-0 gap-y-8">
    <div
      class="px-2 py-3 w-full sm:w-4/5 lg:w-5/12 border-[1px] border-oak rounded-md flex items-center justify-center">
      <div id="{{ generateUUID }}"
        class="relative w-[98%] sm:w-[97%] lg:w-[97%] xl:w-[98%] 2xl:w-[99%] sample-board aspect-square after:content-[''] after:duration-500 after:w-full after:h-full after:absolute after:inset-0 after:backdrop-blur-lg after:z-10 after:rounded-md after:opacity-0"
        data-piece="queen" data-type="movements"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="w-full lg:w-7/12 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-10">
        <h2 class="mb-4 font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-center uppercase sm:text-left sm:text-4xl text-oak">How It
          Moves</h2>
        <hr class="w-4/5 mx-auto border-2 sm:w-full lg:w-4/5 border-oak sm:mx-0">
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-lg text-center sm:text-left">
        <p>
          The queen moves like both a rook and a bishop, allowing it to control both ranks and files as well as
          diagonals.
        </p>
        <p>
          The queen can move any number of squares in a straight line, but it cannot jump over other pieces. It is
          particularly powerful when placed on the same rank or file as another rook, forming a <span
            class="font-bold">battery</span>.
        </p>
        <p>
          The queen is also a key piece in endgames, where its ability to control open files and ranks can lead to
          decisive advantages.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

